<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="188" pageId="2" pageNumber="187" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="187">
<paragraph blockId="2.[828,1437,1763,2076]" pageId="2" pageNumber="187">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="187">
1 Temples very long, seven times as long as eyes. Median lobe of aedeagus very wide, sharply narrowed toward apex (see 
<bibRefCitation author="GUSAROV V. I." box="[967,1134,1827,1851]" pageId="2" pageNumber="187" pagination="431 - 446" refId="ref2594" refString="GUSAROV V. I. 1994: New and little-known Palaearctic Paederinae (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (Nouvelle Serie) 30: 431 - 446." type="journal article" year="1994">GuSAROV 1994</bibRefCitation>
: Figs 37–38). Body length: 
<quantity box="[858,954,1859,1883]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.46" pageId="2" pageNumber="187" unit="mm" value="14.6">14.6 mm</quantity>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[964,1071,1859,1883]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="187">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
. ........ 
<taxonomicName authority="Gusarov, 1994" authorityName="Gusarov" authorityYear="1994" box="[1141,1436,1859,1883]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scimbalium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beloussovi">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1141,1280,1859,1883]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="187">S. beloussovi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="GUSAROV V. I." box="[1286,1436,1859,1883]" pageId="2" pageNumber="187" pagination="431 - 446" refId="ref2594" refString="GUSAROV V. I. 1994: New and little-known Palaearctic Paederinae (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (Nouvelle Serie) 30: 431 - 446." type="journal article" year="1994">Gusarov, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[828,1437,1763,2076]" pageId="2" pageNumber="187">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="187">– Temples significantly shorter, three to four times as long as eyes. In species with described male, median lobe of aedeagus narrower, gradually narrowed toward apex. .. 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="188" pageId="2" pageNumber="187">
<paragraph blockId="2.[828,1437,1763,2076]" pageId="2" pageNumber="187">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="187">
2 Head distinctly longer than wide. Humeral projections poorly developed (
<figureCitation box="[1056,1118,2019,2043]" captionStart="Figs 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,188,1539,1558]" captionTargetBox="[183,1407,195,1518]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[175,1412,189,1527]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–12. Scymbalopsis persica sp. nov. and S. kirghizica Gusarov, 1994. 1–2 – dorsal habitus (1 – S. persica sp. nov., holotype; 2 – S. kirghizica). 3–11 – morphology of S.persica sp. nov.: 3–5 – aedeagus (3–4 – paratype, parameral and lateral view; 5 – holotype); 6–11 – abdominal segments, dorsal view (6–10) or ventral view (11): 6 – male tergite VIII, 7 – male sternite VIII, 8 – male tergite IX and X, 9 – female tergite VIII, 10 – female sternite VIII, 11 – female genital segment. 12 – type locality of S. persica sp. nov. in Lorestan, Iran. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (Figs 1–2), 0.25 mm (Figs 3–11)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4505279" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4505279/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="187">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Body length: 
<quantity box="[1278,1432,2019,2043]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.47" metricValueMax="1.48" metricValueMin="1.46" pageId="2" pageNumber="187" unit="mm" value="14.7" valueMax="14.8" valueMin="14.6">14.6–14.8 mm</quantity>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[858,980,2052,2076]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="2" pageNumber="187">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
. ........................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Gusarov, 1994" authorityName="Gusarov V. I. Gusarov" authorityYear="1994" box="[1145,1436,2051,2075]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scymbalopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kirghizica">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1145,1279,2051,2075]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="187">S. kirghizica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="GUSAROV V. I." box="[1286,1436,2051,2075]" pageId="2" pageNumber="187" pagination="431 - 446" refId="ref2594" refString="GUSAROV V. I. 1994: New and little-known Palaearctic Paederinae (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (Nouvelle Serie) 30: 431 - 446." type="journal article" year="1994">Gusarov, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,760,190,662]" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="188">– Head about as long as wide. Humeral projections well developed. ........................................................................ 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="188">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,760,190,662]" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="188">
3 Temples three times as long as eyes. Pronotum slightly longer than wide, markedly narrowed posteriad, with moderately sparse and fine punctation. Body yellowish-brown, with slightly darker head and pronotum. Apical part of median lobe of aedeagus relatively wide (
<figureCitation box="[247,342,414,438]" captionStart="Figs 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,188,1539,1558]" captionTargetBox="[183,1407,195,1518]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[175,1412,189,1527]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–12. Scymbalopsis persica sp. nov. and S. kirghizica Gusarov, 1994. 1–2 – dorsal habitus (1 – S. persica sp. nov., holotype; 2 – S. kirghizica). 3–11 – morphology of S.persica sp. nov.: 3–5 – aedeagus (3–4 – paratype, parameral and lateral view; 5 – holotype); 6–11 – abdominal segments, dorsal view (6–10) or ventral view (11): 6 – male tergite VIII, 7 – male sternite VIII, 8 – male tergite IX and X, 9 – female tergite VIII, 10 – female sternite VIII, 11 – female genital segment. 12 – type locality of S. persica sp. nov. in Lorestan, Iran. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (Figs 1–2), 0.25 mm (Figs 3–11)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4505279" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4505279/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">Figs 3, 5</figureCitation>
). Body length: 
<quantity box="[508,665,414,438]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.315" metricValueMax="1.41" metricValueMin="1.22" pageId="3" pageNumber="188" unit="mm" value="13.149999999999999" valueMax="14.1" valueMin="12.2">12.2–14.1 mm</quantity>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[237,297,446,470]" captionStart="Figs 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,188,1539,1558]" captionTargetBox="[183,1407,195,1518]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[175,1412,189,1527]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–12. Scymbalopsis persica sp. nov. and S. kirghizica Gusarov, 1994. 1–2 – dorsal habitus (1 – S. persica sp. nov., holotype; 2 – S. kirghizica). 3–11 – morphology of S.persica sp. nov.: 3–5 – aedeagus (3–4 – paratype, parameral and lateral view; 5 – holotype); 6–11 – abdominal segments, dorsal view (6–10) or ventral view (11): 6 – male tergite VIII, 7 – male sternite VIII, 8 – male tergite IX and X, 9 – female tergite VIII, 10 – female sternite VIII, 11 – female genital segment. 12 – type locality of S. persica sp. nov. in Lorestan, Iran. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (Figs 1–2), 0.25 mm (Figs 3–11)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4505279" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4505279/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[307,354,447,470]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">Iran</collectingCountry>
. ............................... 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[568,760,446,470]" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">
<taxonomicName authority="Shavrin &amp; Anichtchenko, 2019" authorityName="Shavrin &amp; Anichtchenko" authorityYear="2019" box="[568,671,446,470]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scymbalopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="188" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[568,671,446,470]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">S. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[677,760,446,470]" pageId="3" pageNumber="188" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,760,190,662]" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="188">
– Temples four times as long as eyes. Pronotum distinctly longer than wide, slightly narrowed posteriad, with dense and moderately large punctation. Body reddish- brown. Apical part of median lobe of aedeagus narrow (see 
<bibRefCitation author="GUSAROV V. I." box="[234,403,606,630]" pageId="3" pageNumber="188" pagination="431 - 446" refId="ref2594" refString="GUSAROV V. I. 1994: New and little-known Palaearctic Paederinae (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (Nouvelle Serie) 30: 431 - 446." type="journal article" year="1994">GuSAROV 1994</bibRefCitation>
: Figs 31–32). Body length: 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" pageId="3" pageNumber="188" unit="mm" value="11.5">11.5 mm</quantity>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[237,359,638,662]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
. ............... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Jakobson, 1909)" baseAuthorityName="Jakobson" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[472,759,638,662]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scimbalium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="188" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reitteri">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[472,574,638,662]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">S. reitteri</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="JAKOBSON G. G." box="[587,752,638,662]" pageId="3" pageNumber="188" pagination="481 - 560" refId="ref2629" refString="JAKOBSON G. G. 1909: Fasc. 7. Pp. 481 - 560. In: Zhuki Rossii i zapadnoy Evropy [Beetles of Russia and western Europe]. A. F. Devrien, St. Petersburg, 1024 pp. + 83 pl. (in Russian)." type="book chapter" year="1909">Jakobson, 1909</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
